(130, 1, '2021-12-23 21:09:08', '2021-12-23 21:09:08', '<!-- wp:sensei-lms/button-contact-teacher -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-contact-teacher is-style-outline wp-block-sensei-button wp-block-button has-text-align-left\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Contact Teacher</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:sensei-lms/button-contact-teacher -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Questions can be added in one of two ways - by going to <em>Questions</em> &gt; <em>Add New</em>, or by adding them directly to a quiz. Although this lesson covers the latter, configuring questions is the same regardless of which method is used.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To add questions to a quiz, create a new lesson by going to <em>Lessons</em> &gt; <em>Add New</em>. You will see that the quiz block has already been added to the page for you. <em>(Note: For managing questions using the legacy meta box rather than blocks, please refer to <a href=\"#legacy\">this documentation</a>.)</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Question Types</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The default question type that is added to a quiz is multiple choice. You can change this by clicking inside the question and selecting an alternate type from the toolbar dropdown:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4485,\"width\":425,\"height\":478,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/quiz-block-question-type-selector.jpg?w=850\" alt=\"Quiz block - Question type selector\" class=\"wp-image-4485\" width=\"425\" height=\"478\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After selecting a question type, the editor will update to show the appropriate answer section for that type.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Multiple Choice</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Multiple choice questions list a set of possible answers that the learner can choose from. This question type supports multiple correct and incorrect answers. If a question has more than one correct answer, the learner must select all of them in order to pass (if a passmark is required).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can add as many answers as you like to a multiple choice question. Click the <em>Right</em> / <em>Wrong</em> toggles beside each answer to indicate whether that answer is correct or incorrect. If there is more than one correct answer, the radio buttons will change to check boxes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4538,\"width\":735,\"height\":416,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/question-block-multiple-choice.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Question block - Multiple Choice\" class=\"wp-image-4538\" width=\"735\" height=\"416\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also show the answers in a different&nbsp;order every time the quiz is viewed by selecting the <em>Random Order</em> checkbox in the settings sidebar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>True/False</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>True/False questions are the simplest question type and take either a true or false answer. The correct answer can be set by clicking the <em>Right</em> / <em>Wrong</em> toggles next to an answer:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4546,\"width\":735,\"height\":347,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/question-block-true-false.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Question block - True/False\" class=\"wp-image-4546\" width=\"735\" height=\"347\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Gap Fill</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gap fill requires a learner to fill in the blank, where the \"gap\" represents the acceptable answers. Multiple correct answers can be specified by typing a comma or pressing the <em>Enter</em> key after entering an answer:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4548,\"width\":735,\"height\":342,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/question-block-gap-fill.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Question block - Gap Fill\" class=\"wp-image-4548\" width=\"735\" height=\"342\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Single Line</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Single line&nbsp;questions&nbsp;enable learners to enter their answer into a single line text field:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4550,\"width\":735,\"height\":311,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/question-block-single-line.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Question block - Single Line\" class=\"wp-image-4550\" width=\"735\" height=\"311\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Multi Line</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Multi line&nbsp;questions&nbsp;are open-ended questions that enable learners to enter their answer into a multi-line text field:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4554,\"width\":735,\"height\":339,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/question-block-multi-line.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Question block - Multi Line\" class=\"wp-image-4554\" width=\"735\" height=\"339\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>File Upload</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The file upload question type enables your learners to upload a file or document as their answer. <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Uploading_Files\">Supported file types are controlled by WordPress</a>. Examples include images, documents, audio and video files:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":4555,\"width\":735,\"height\":345,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/question-block-file-upload.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Question block - File Upload\" class=\"wp-image-4555\" width=\"735\" height=\"345\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Settings</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each question type has individual settings that can be configured. Some of these settings are common to several types:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><em>Grade</em> - All question types have a grade setting that configures the number of points to assign to a question. For example, you could assign a higher point value to more difficult questions, while easier ones would have a lower value. The grade can be set from either the toolbar or the sidebar by typing a new value, or clicking the up and down arrows.</li><li><em>Answer Feedback</em> - Answer feedback is only applicable for multiple choice, true/false and gap fill questions. This feedback is shown to learners after they submit a quiz that is graded automatically. For manual grading, the answer feedback can be customized when the quiz is graded.</li><li><em>Grading Notes</em> - Grading notes are only applicable for single line, multi line and file upload questions. They are displayed to the teacher when grading the question to provide some guidance on the expected answer.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" />\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"legacy\">Question Management - Legacy*</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*<em>This section is only applicable for those who are still using the legacy meta boxes, rather than blocks, to manage questions.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Questions can be added independently of a quiz, making it possible to use them across multiple quizzes. To add a question:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Go to&nbsp;<em>Questions&nbsp;</em>&gt;&nbsp;<em>Add New</em>.</li><li>Enter the question in the <em>Question</em> field.</li><li>Enter an optional<em> Description</em>.</li><li>Select a type from the <em>Question Type</em> dropdown.</li><li>Update the<em> Grade</em>. This should be a number greater than or equal to 0.</li><li>Enter the answer to the question. The exact format will depend on the type of question that was selected.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Question Types</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of different question types to choose from:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Multiple Choice</li><li>True/False</li><li>Gap Fill</li><li>Single Line</li><li>Multi Line</li><li>File Upload</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Multiple Choice</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Multiple choice questions support multiple right and wrong answers. If a question has more than one correct answer, the learner must select all of them in order to pass (if a passmark is required).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Selecting&nbsp;<em>Randomise answer order</em>&nbsp;will display the options in a different&nbsp;order every time the quiz is viewed:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":3183,\"width\":735,\"height\":397,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/multiple-choice.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Multiple choice\" class=\"wp-image-3183\" width=\"735\" height=\"397\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>True/False</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>True/false questions are the simplest question type and take either a true or false answer:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":3181,\"width\":735,\"height\":371,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/true-false.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"True/false\" class=\"wp-image-3181\" width=\"735\" height=\"371\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Gap Fill</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gap fill is a fill-in-the-blank question type, where the \"gap\" is the blank that needs to be filled in by the learner. If there is more than one possible answer, or you want to account for common spelling mistakes, you can add the answer as a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_expression\">regular expression</a>. The most common use of this would be to list all possible correct answers, with each one separated by a | symbol:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":3184,\"width\":735,\"height\":371,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/gap-fill.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Gap fill\" class=\"wp-image-3184\" width=\"735\" height=\"371\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a gap-fill question is auto-graded, the case and leading/trailing spaces are ignored. In the example above, both \" Counts\" and \"Beats \" are acceptable answers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Single Line</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Single line&nbsp;questions&nbsp;allow learners to enter their answer into a text box that is restricted to a single&nbsp;line&nbsp;of text:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":3185,\"width\":735,\"height\":341,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/single-line.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Single line\" class=\"wp-image-3185\" width=\"735\" height=\"341\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Multi Line</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Multi line&nbsp;questions are open-ended&nbsp;questions that allow learners to enter their answer into a multi-line text box:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":3187,\"width\":735,\"height\":344,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/multi-line.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"Multi line\" class=\"wp-image-3187\" width=\"735\" height=\"344\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>File Upload</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The file upload question type allows you to have your learners upload a file or document as their answer. <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Uploading_Files\">Supported file types are controlled by WordPress</a>, but examples include images, documents, audio and video files:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":3188,\"width\":735,\"height\":346,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://senseilms.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/file-upload.jpg?w=980\" alt=\"File upload\" class=\"wp-image-3188\" width=\"735\" height=\"346\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Settings</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Grade</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Grade is the value you would like to assign to the question. For example, you could give a higher grade to more difficult questions, while easier ones would have a lower score.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Questions can also be assigned a grade of 0. Questions with a zero grade are skipped during auto-grading.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Media</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A media file can be included as part of a question. Images, audio and video files are displayed inline within the question. All other types of media are displayed as links. Additionally, the title and description of the media item, if specified, are displayed below the media. By default, images use the <em>Medium size</em> width and height settings as defined in&nbsp;<em>Settings</em> &gt; <em>Media</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Answer Feedback</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Answer feedback is applicable for multiple choice and true/false questions. This feedback is shown to learners after they submit a quiz that&nbsp;is set to grade automatically. For manual grading, the answer feedback can be customized when the quiz is graded.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"question-categories\">Question Categories</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question categories make it easier to find relevant questions to <a href=\"https://senseilms.com/lesson/quizzes#category-questions\">add to a quiz</a>. A category can be added to a question by selecting one or more categories in the <em>Question Categories</em> panel. A new category can be added by clicking the <em>+ Add New Question Category</em> link.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question categories can be managed by going to <em>Questions</em> &gt; <em>Categories</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:sensei-lms/lesson-actions -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-lesson-actions\"><div class=\"sensei-buttons-container\"><!-- wp:sensei-lms/button-view-quiz {\"inContainer\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-view-quiz is-style-default sensei-buttons-container__button-block wp-block-sensei-lms-button-view-quiz__wrapper\"><div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-view-quiz is-style-default wp-block-sensei-button wp-block-button has-text-align-left\"><button class=\"wp-block-button__link\">View Quiz</button></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:sensei-lms/button-view-quiz -->\n\n<!-- wp:sensei-lms/button-complete-lesson {\"inContainer\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-complete-lesson is-style-default sensei-buttons-container__button-block wp-block-sensei-lms-button-complete-lesson__wrapper\"><div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-complete-lesson is-style-default wp-block-sensei-button wp-block-button has-text-align-left\"><button class=\"wp-block-button__link sensei-stop-double-submission\">Complete Lesson</button></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:sensei-lms/button-complete-lesson -->\n\n<!-- wp:sensei-lms/button-next-lesson {\"inContainer\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-next-lesson is-style-default sensei-buttons-container__button-block wp-block-sensei-lms-button-next-lesson__wrapper\"><div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-next-lesson is-style-default wp-block-sensei-button wp-block-button has-text-align-left\"><button class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Next Lesson</button></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:sensei-lms/button-next-lesson -->\n\n<!-- wp:sensei-lms/button-reset-lesson {\"inContainer\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-reset-lesson is-style-outline sensei-buttons-container__button-block wp-block-sensei-lms-button-reset-lesson__wrapper\"><div class=\"wp-block-sensei-lms-button-reset-lesson is-style-outline wp-block-sensei-button wp-block-button has-text-align-left\"><button class=\"wp-block-button__link sensei-stop-double-submission\">Reset Lesson</button></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:sensei-lms/button-reset-lesson --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:sensei-lms/lesson-actions -->', 'Questions', 'Learn how to create and manage questions in Sensei LMS.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'questions', '', '', '2021-12-23 21:09:08', '2021-12-23 21:09:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/lesson/questions/', 0, 'lesson', '', 0),
